    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n359" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἶσα</span></b> : allotted
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">share</span>, or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">portion, lot, term of life,
            destiny;</span> prov. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐν καρὸς αἴσῃ</span>
          (cf. Att. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐν οὐδενὸς μέρει</span>); <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κατ᾽ αι&lt;&gt;͂σαν</span>, ‘as much as was
          my due,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οὐδ᾽ ὑπὲρ αἶσαν,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 6.333</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ὑπὲρ
            Διὸς αἶσαν,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 17.321</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ὁμῇ πεπρωμένος αἴσῃ</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            15.209</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
